msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: An incomplete collection of prayers and incantations, mostly labeled as fāʼidah with explanations of when to use them and what their benefits are. Item is missing pages and is disordered.

msItem.title: Incomplete text of prayers and incantations.

supportDesc.foliation: Unfoliated; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed.

decoNote: Rubrications in red; some magic squares and other diagrams in red and black.

binding.p: Item is disbound; some gatherings are still sewn; no covers.

origin.p: Item is undated, perhaps 17th or 18th century.

history.provenance: Purchased from Addison and Sarova Auctioneers 30 March 2019, lot 1021.
